cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.DS, cs.AI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a technique for scaling up Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), a popular topic modeling technique used in machine learning. It also uses variational inference, which is a common technique in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as LDA is often used in information retrieval to discover topics in large document collections. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language) as topic modeling is a common technique in natural language processing. 

It may also fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper proposes a method for efficiently distributing computation in a large dataset. 

Finally, it could be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as LDA is a technique used in AI for unsupervised learning and the paper proposes a scalable solution for this technique.
